The paper deals with representation learning and generative models, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of invertible neural networks and nonlinear ICA also suggests a focus on deep learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also includes experiments on image data, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the separation of informative latent variables from noise, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical properties of the proposed method, which suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT).
